I agree with the war on the logo being a big thing, but you are wrong on
other manufactures not doing the same. 30 years ago when I was heavy into
Chevy, Ford, and Mopar, you could find aftermarket items with OEM style
logos on them. Then WHAM, the industry as a whole clamped down on parts
makers, using the federal government, and put a cease and desist on all
logo'ized parts not OEM. Well, there went my OEM look a like hubcaps etc. 

Even though the ads in all of the sources you described don't contain the
logo anymore, the ads are still there, and they are still in business. In
fact, I counted 7 new ads in my March Hot VW than in my January. The logo
may be out, but the market is still there and growing.
67 Single Cab, DP 1641cc 34PICT
71 Trike 1776cc 32/36 Progressive
VolksAir 1585cc 28 PICT
Ray, Kent WA
