Yeah,
I won't argue with you regarding the supply and demand issue.  That's a
given, somewhere somehow a part will be made/found.  At what cost?  whether
it be now or 10 years from now?

VWOA is CURRENTLY on a tirade of shutting down personal/business websites
all over the web.  If it has a VW logo, uses the word VW, Volkswagen,
bug...etc etc...on and on...they are shutting them down.
Look at your magazines....see any ad with VW logo seatbelts? mudflaps?
Shit, look at the ad for Wolfgang.  A friggin' singlecab--made by VW can't
be pictured with it's own logo on the front?  It's getting ridiculous no
matter how you look at it.

There are lawsuits galore against parthouses, shops etc. for unauthorized
use of their logo.

Damn...the newsgroup ramva had a cease and desist order against their logo.

Look in a Hot Rod magazine or a Street Rodder.  All kinds of
Ford/Chevy/Dodge parts houses, ads, etc.  No threat there, is there?.  Are
ACVW's that much of a threat to VW?!  Where's a little support? 

Don't get me wrong...I am a freelance Graphic Designer and know all to well
about copyright/trademark laws.  But have they forgotten what got them to
where they are today? 

Again regarding parts......
We all know that they are out there, and will be made by someone.
But what about, when you want to replace you VW hubcap years down the
road...who knows maybe smoothies will only be available, or you have to
restore some og ones.  Or how about just trying to replace your VW logo on
the front of the bus, or script on the rear?   VW keeps it up, who knows
where these little parts will be? or how much?

I see a lot of buses around here, and deal with them on a daily basis due to
the list and internet.  But in reality, our buses are rare.  And they are
only getting older everyday.  The demand WILL NOT be there 20 years from
now, when there are even less on the road.  I sure as hell hope I won't be
paying 200 bucks for a front brake cylinder in 20 years, just to keep my bus
on the road.
We definatley need VW's support..or at least their blessing for this hobby
to have a strong future years down the road.

I'm only 28 and got into VW's when I was 16.  I did cause they were cheap
and easy to work on.  

At least I've still got one out of the two.

Beto
63EZ

